cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the task of monocular depth estimation using deep learning methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses adversarial learning and domain adaptation, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of fully-convolutional architectures, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses the use of unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
